<1ST_LINE>r w BC-HouseCivilRightsRollCall 3Takes   03-23 0481</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-House Civil Rights Roll Call, 3 Takes,</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 292-133 roll call Tuesday by which
the House voted to override President Reagan's veto and enacted the
Civil Rights Restoration Act.
   A ``yes'' vote is to override the veto and enact the law.
   Voting yes were 240 Democrats and 52 Republicans.
   Voting no were 10 Democrats and 123 Republicans.
   xxx denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are two vacancies in the 435-member House.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>ALABAMA</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Democrats _ Bevill, yes; Erdreich, yes; Flippo, yes; Harris,
yes; Nichols, yes.
   Republicans _ Callahan, no; Dickinson, no.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>ALASKA</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Republican _ Young, yes.
