<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Stable Fire,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Kills Dozens of Horses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WACONIA, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire in a hay-filled barn killed 70
breeding horses in an adjoining stable, authorities said.
   Owner Ward Holasek said he suffered burns as he ran through the
stable to get some of the horses out. He, his wife, veterinarian
Georgene Holasek, and workers were able to save 12 horses, said
Fire Chief Randy Sorenson.
   The stable included horses brought in for breeding from as far
away as California and New York, Georgene Holasek said. Most of the
horses killed were Arabian and were worth about $10,000 apiece.
Some, including a prized breeding stallion belonging to the couple,
had even higher values, the owners said.
   The loss from Tuesday's blaze, which took 90 minutes to control,
was estimated at $1.2 million, Sorensen said.
   The cause of the fire was under investigation.
</TEXT>
