<1ST_LINE>r a PM-IrishRescue     03-23 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Irish Rescue,0166</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dublin, Ireland, Firefighters Rescue Women In Dublin, Ga.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The luck o' the Irish was with two elderly
women who were trapped in their overturned car. They were rescued
by six firefighters from Dublin, Ireland.
   Azzie Harrison, 72, and passenger Edna Rozar, 73, of Dublin,
Ga., became trapped Tuesday after their car plunged over the side
of a bridge into a creek near the intersection of U.S. 80 West and
Shamrock Drive.
   Six members of the Dublin, Ireland, Fire Brigade, who are
visiting to bring greetings from their lord mayor for the
millennium of their Irish hometown, were sitting in a fire station
when the rescue call came.
   They joined in cutting through the car's hood and breaking its
windows to free the women, who were listed in fair condition early
today at a hospital.
   ``That's the thing about firefighters,'' said Seamus O'Connor,
one of the six firemen. ``We can go anywhere and fit right in.''
</TEXT>
