<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gerhard Claas, general secretary of the
Baptist World Alliance, died Monday from injuries suffered in a
traffic accident near Lodi, Calif.
   Claas, 59, was the chief administrative officer of the alliance,
an international Baptist organization with a membership of more
than 35 million worldwide. The organization conducts teaching,
development and disaster relief efforts in Third World nations.
   Claas was a citizen of West Germany, where he had served in a
number of pastoral and administrative posts.
