<HEAD>Bhaktipada's Book Urges Celibacy</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: CORRECTS typo in dateline.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW VRINDABAN, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Just say no to sex. That's the idea
being promoted in a new book by the leader of the nation's largest
Hare Krishna community.
   Kirtanananda Swami Bhaktipada on Tuesday said he's looking for a
publisher for his work, titled ``The Joy of No Sex,'' in which he
urges people to practice celibacy.
   ``Sexual pleasure is a perversion of the real pleasure, which is
spiritual living,'' said Bhaktipada, spiritual leader of 700
Krishna devotees at New Vrindaban.
   He said people should engage in sex only to procreate.
   The national epidemic of fear over AIDS will make his ideas more
palatable in the United States, Bhaktipada said. In addition, he
said he will mail a copy of the book to Pope John Paul II.

