<HEAD>Iran Urges Revolution in Occupied Territories</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Recasts 1st graf.</NOTE>
<HEAD>With AM-Israel, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JAMAL HALABY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>AMMAN, Jordan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Iranian delegate said Wednesday the
Palestinians in Israel's occupied territories should emulate Iran's
Islamic revolution and destroy their enemy.
   Mohammed Ali Taskhiri addressed a conference of the 46-member
Organization of Islamic Conference, which has issued a statement
about the Palestinian rebellion but is is not expected to make
headway toward a truce in the Iran-Iraq war. The Persian Gulf
neighbors have been fighting since September 1980.
   Taskhiri cited the revolution of Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini
against the pro-U.S. regime of the late Shah Mohammad Reza Pahlavi,
which he called a ``nest of evil.'' The shah was ousted in February
1979.
