stones in Palestine, who are facing the enemy with his American
weapons,'' Taskhiri said.
   ``The Zionist enemy is killing our children, is burning their
bodies and breaking their arms and burying them alive,'' he said of
the rebellion in the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip, which began
Dec. 8. More than 100 Arabs have been killed.
   ``Palestine is a Moslem issue,'' he said. ``It is the main
issue, but we haven't done anything about it yet except talk about
it.''
   His reference was to a statement issued by the delegates Tuesday
that condemned Israel's ``oppressive and criminal'' measures and
advocated political and financial support for the protesters.
   It did not say what form the aid should take or whether it would
be forthcoming.
   Iran claims the rebellion is inspired by Islam, but observers
say opposition to Israeli occupation is the chief motivation.
