<HEAD>76 Percent Of Hard Red Winter Wheat Graded No. 1 Or No. 2</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A study of last year's wheat quality showed
that 76 percent of the hard red winter wheat samples graded No. 1
or No. 2, compared with 70 percent in 1986, the Agriculture
Department said Wednesday.
   For hard red spring wheat, 75 percent graded No. 1, compared
with 70 percent in 1986, the department's Federal Grain Inspection
Service said.
   The annual survey involved 12,739 wheat samples from the 1987
crop, said W. Kirk Miller, administrator of the agency. The samples
were taken during the first four weeks following local harvests
around the country.
