<HEAD>London Shares Down 7 Points</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were lower at midday Wednesday,
depressed by continued lack of trading volume and concern about a
further rise in the value of the pound.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was down 7.0
points, or 0.4 percent, at 1,828.4.
   Volume was light at 221.2 million shares, compared with 211.7
million at the same time Tuesday.
   The pound's rise was ``holding everything back,'' one dealer
said, adding that many investors were waiting to see if the Bank of
England would take further steps to halt the currency's rise. The
central bank cleared the way last week for a half-point cut in
commercial banks' base lending rate to 8.5 percent.
