<2ND_LINE>BC-Burlington Sells,0242</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Agrees to Sell Two European Businesses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Burlington Industries Inc. Wednesday
announced it has signed definitive agreements for the sale of its
two European businesses, which have manufacturing operations in
Ireland and Italy.
   Burlington said it has agreed to sell Burlington Sportswear
Fabrics Limited to Royal Nijverdal-Ten Cate N.V., of the
Netherlands. It said it has also agreed to sell Klopman
International S.p.A. to Dominion Textile of Canada.
   Terms of the deals were not disclosed, but the announcement said
the financing necessary to complete the transactions was committed
to the buyers by financial institutions.
   The sales are subject to approval by the Irish and Italian
governments.
   Burlington Sportswear Fabrics Limited is one of Europe's largest
manufacturers of denim fabrics for men's, women's and children's
wear. It has plants at Longford and Tullamore, Ireland.
   Ten Cate is a diversified manufacturer of textile and plastic
products which is headquartered in Almelo, the Netherlands, and has
extensive operations in the Netherlands and other countries.
   Klopman International S.p.A. is the leading European producer of
finished polyester-cotton fabrics for the uniform, leisure wear and
active wear markets. It has plants in Frosinone, Italy, and in
Tralee and Gillope, Ireland.
   Dominion Textile Inc. is a diversified textile manufacturer with
headquarters in Montreal and was a partner with New York financier
Asher Edelman in an unsuccessful attempt to buy out Burlington last
year.
</TEXT>
