<HEAD>Board Of Directors Approves Restructuring Plan To Sell Off Casinos</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 8th graf pvs The chairman...to CORRECT that company is
negotiating to terminate its management contract and to DELETE
reference to Los Angeles and Hong Kong investors. Picks up 9th
graf, Recreational properties...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Del E. Webb Corp. announced Wednesday its
board of directors approved a restructuring plan that includes
selling off its casinos and other leisure operations and focusing
instead on real estate.
   ``In recent years, Webb's most profitable operations on a
continuing basis have been real-estate oriented and particularly
our adult community developments,'' said Philip J. Dion, the
corporation's chairman. ``This, our greatest past and present
strength, is where we will concentrate our efforts.''
   ``Present shareholder value will be maximized by the sale of our
leisure facilities and use of the proceeds to strengthen the
company's balance sheet and provide the capital necessary to
continue expansion of our real estate business,'' Dion said.
   The leisure operations the Phoenix-based company owns and
manages had revenue of $171 million in 1987, $127 million from the
three Nevada casino hotels and $44 million from recreational
properties, Dion said.
   Gaming includes three casino hotels in Nevada which Del Webb
will reacquire complete control of next month _ the Mint in Las
Vegas, the High Sierra at Lake Tahoe and the Nevada Club in
Laughlin.
   Dion said the three casinos were sold to two limited
partnerships run by Webb executives in 1984.
   He said the reacquisition will allow for the orderly disposition
of the properties by simplifying the ownership structure.
   The company also is negotiating with the limited partnership
that owns the Claridge Hotel and Casino in Atlantic City, N.J., to
terminate Webb's contract to manage the hotel.
   Recreational properties the company owns and operates include
five marinas on Lake Powell in Arizona and Utah, and Wilderness
River Adventures, a river-rafting company on the Colorado River.
   When the restructuring is complete, Dion said the company will
consist of Del E. Webb Communities Inc. and Del E. Webb Commercial
Properties Corp. The communities concern is the developer of Sun
City West Vistro in Arizona and Sun City Summerlin, an adult
community in Las Vegas.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
